Scam. The app times itself out within 1 minute this will be unchangeable. I leave my screen timeout preference at "do not time out" so I can watch longer videos on youtube or listen to long meditations... So the app performing this way has nothing to do with your phone settings. And the app offers no way to stretch the timeout time. I really enjoyed the old version of GhostRadar which was FREE and woukd run for hours like a chatty cathy. This app sucks ass. Its 1/10th of the previous. No.

Spudpickles Ghost Radar Apps are the absolute best. I had classic an legacy before, and recently got this one. Pretty impressive, actually. Better accuracy than any app like it that I've tried, and I have tried a lot. Our paranormal investigation teams uses this app religiously and we all swear by it. Keep up the excellent work, Spudpickles! You guys are awesome!

The Augusta, Georgia Ghost Trolly is the very best haunted tour I've been a part of and it's great to see this amazing app refitted for it. Ghost Radar is a really incredible and thought-provoking app which is sure to get everyone involved and add a heavy dose of creepiness to the trolley experience. I'll definitely be using it on the tour this Halloween season!

I downloaded this app while talking with a friend at the Imperial Theatre in downtown Augusta, we were speaking of Edgar Allen Poe and one of his cousin's connection to Augusta. Some short time later as the conversation drifted to other topics, I turned the app on and one of the first couple of words that came forth was "writer". Interesting. Later on while standing next to the light board the word "cat" was uttered, the lightboard operator's name is Caron and her nickname?  Cat.  Very interesting app.
